COMP2011_ch7_7:
Array and Control
Array works particularly well with loops: e.g., use a for-loop to
access and manipulate each array element in turn.
This is not a coincidence, but part of the C++ language
design.
Examples
int y;
// A regular int variable
int x[3];
// An array of 3 int numbers
x[0] = 34;
// Array indices start from zero in C++
x[1] = 289;
x[2] = 75;
// Index of the last element is 2 NOT 3!
y = x[2];
// Now both y and x[2] are 75
max(x[2], x[0]);
// Pass array elements by value
swap(x[1], x[0]);
// Pass array elements by reference
for (int j = 0; j < 3; j++)
x[j] *= 3;
// Triple each element of an array
